<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                    <head>No. 175.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sargent</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-02-15"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 15,
                            1883</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>The President invites Germany to send a commission of experts to the United
                        States to examine raising and packing of hogs and hog products for food. He
                        asks that final decision in prohibitory measures be suspended until
                        commission can adequately report.</p>
                    <p>Instruction by mail.</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>